merge the csv files using power query into one file which can be handled by Excel 
split the long strings using textsplit(cell,",") which is more efficient than SQL's substring(charindex)   in this particular data
removing "[" and "]" and "'" from both ends of  the string  using  =SUBSTITUTE(SUBSTITUTE(SUBSTITUTE(cells, "'", ""), "[", ""), "]", "")
fix overlapped columns 
there are mobiles without original price >>>> offer price + offer price * off now
perform some additional cleaning  like removing duplicates, unifying values and names , removing Nulls and blanks etc
